'''Al Ramadi Stadium''', is a multi-use stadium in [[Ramadi]], Iraq.  It is currently used mostly for [[association football|football]] matches and serves as the home stadium of [[Al Ramadi FC]].  The stadium holds 15,000 people.<ref>[http://www.worldfootball.net/venues/al-ramadi-stadium-baghdad/ World Football.net]</ref>

In May 2015 the stadium was blown up in a terrorist attack by [[ISIS]].

The construction of a new Olympic Stadium west of the city can accommodate 30,000 spectators, stopped working after the events of [[Al Anbar Governorate|Anbar]] it was wrecking by [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|ISIS]]. After the Iraqi government regained control over the city, mass graves were discovered in the stadium.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://stadiumdb.com/news/2016/04/iraq_shocking_findings_at_ramadi_stadium|publisher=Stadium DB|title=Iraq: Shocking findings at Ramadi stadium|date=23 April 2016}}</ref>

