'''Amanat Baghdad''' ({{lang-ar|'''نادي امانة بغداد'''}}), is an [[Iraq]]i football team based in [[Karkh|Karkh District]], West Districts of the [[Tigris River]], [[Baghdad]].

==History==
*On July 1, 1957, '''Maslahat Naqil Al-Rukab''' ({{lang-ar|'''مصلحة نقل الركاب'''}} ''literally: Passenger Transport Department'') were formed.
*In 1957, '''Amana Al-Asama''' ({{lang-ar|'''امانة العاصمة'''}} ''literally: Capital Secretariat'') were formed.<ref>[http://rsssf.com/tablesi/iraqchamp.html List of Iraqi League Champions]</ref>
*In 1974,  '''Al-Baladiyat''' ({{lang-ar|'''البلديات'''}} ''literally: Municipalities'') were formed by the merger of Maslahat Naqil Al-Rakab and '''Esalet Al-Mai''' ({{lang-ar|'''إساله الماي'''}} ''literally: Water Liquefaction'').<ref>[http://rsssf.com/tablesi/iraq75.html Iraqi League 1974–75]</ref>
*In 1977, '''Al-Amana''' ({{lang-ar|'''الأمانة'''}} ''literally: Secretariat'') were formed by the merger of Al-Baladiyat and Amana Al-Asama.
*On August 5, 2009, Al-Amana renamed to '''Baghdad''' ({{lang-ar|'''بغداد'''}}).
*In 2014, Baghdad renamed to '''Amanat Baghdad''' ({{lang-ar|'''أمانة بغداد'''}} ''literally: Mayoralty of Baghdad'').

==Stadium==
Since 2011 Amanat Baghdad have got their own stadium. The [[Amanat Baghdad Stadium]] holds 5,000 people.

