'''Delta Queens''' is a women's football club in [[Delta State]], [[Nigeria]].<ref>http://www.vanguardngr.com/2009/07/delta-fc-players-earn-one-month-salary-in-a-season/</ref><ref>http://allafrica.com/stories/200612041639.html</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.frontiersnews.com/index.php/sports/39-sports/3422-nigerian-professional-women-continues-as-delta-queens-confronts-fc-robo |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-08-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130509060428/http://frontiersnews.com/index.php/sports/39-sports/3422-nigerian-professional-women-continues-as-delta-queens-confronts-fc-robo |archivedate=2013-05-09 |df= }}</ref><ref>http://www.footballzz.com/equipa.php?id=46437</ref> It is one of the most successful Nigerian clubsides. They compete in the [[Nigeria Women Premier League]], the highest division of female football in the country.<ref>[http://allafrica.com/stories/200612041639.html Nigeria: Delta Queens Crowned FA Cup Champions]</ref>

== History ==
Delta Queens was formed by the government of Governor [[James Ibori]] in January 2000. The administration of the club was headed by Commissioner for Sports, Solomon Ogba.  

