{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Townfield Lane | nickname = | country = England | image =<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Lashings World XI @ Oxton - June 21st 2013.jpg|thumb|right|Lashings World XI @ Oxton - June 2013]] --> | location = [[Oxton, Cheshire|Oxton]], [[Cheshire]] | establishment = 1882 (first recorded match) | seating_capacity = | owner = [[Oxton Cricket Club]] | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1989 | club1 = [[Minor Counties cricket team|Minor Counties]] | year2 = 1895&ndash;2004 | club2 = [[Cheshire County Cricket Club|Cheshire]] | date = 20 August | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/318.html Ground profile }}
'''Townfield Lane''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Oxton, Cheshire|Oxton]], [[Merseyside]] (formerly in [[Cheshire]]). The first recorded match on the ground was in 1882 when Oxton played Huyton.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/318_misc.html Other matches played at Townfield Lane]</ref> The ground was first used by [[Cheshire County Cricket Club|Cheshire]] in 1895 when they played [[Worcestershire County Cricket Club|Worcestershire]] in the [[Minor Counties Championship]]. Cheshire used the ground during a number of periods in the 20th century. They played 49 Minor Counties Championship matches, with the final Minor Counties Championship fixture held on the ground coming in 2004 against [[Devon County Cricket Club|Devon]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/318_minc.html Minor Counties Championship Matches played at Townfield Lane]</ref> The ground has also held 2 [[MCCA Knockout Trophy]] matches; the last of which was between Cheshire and [[Lincolnshire County Cricket Club|Lincolnshire]] in 1987.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/318_mint.html Minor Counties Trophy Matches played at Townfield Lane]</ref>
The ground has also hosted [[List-A cricket|List-A]] matches. The first List-A match on the ground was between Cheshire and [[Yorkshire County Cricket Club|Yorkshire]] in the [[1985 NatWest Trophy]]. Cheshire used the ground for a further List-A match in the [[1986 NatWest Trophy]] against [[Surrey County Cricket Club|Surrey]]. The third and final List-A match played on the ground to date saw a combined [[Minor Counties cricket team|Minor Counties]] team play [[Nottinghamshire County Cricket Club|Nottinghamshire]] in the 1989 [[Benson and Hedges Cup]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/318_a.html List-A Matches played at Townfield Lane]</ref>
In local domestic cricket, the ground is the home venue of [[Oxton Cricket Club]]<ref>[http://www.oxtonsportsclub.com/ Oxton Cricket Club]</ref> who play in the [[Cheshire County Cricket League]].
