{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = Stade Général Aboubacar Sangoulé Lamizana | nickname = | image = Stadiumbobodioulasso1.jpg | image_size = 280px | location = [[Bobo Dioulasso]], [[Burkina Faso]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = | opened = 1998 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = [[grass]] | Constructor = | construction_cost = | architect = | former_names = Stade Omnisports de Bobo-Dioulasso (1998-2010) | nicknames = | tenants = [[RC Bobo Dioulasso]] (1998-present) | seating_capacity = 30,000 | dimensions = }}
'''Stade Général Aboubacar Sangoulé Lamizana''' is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Bobo Dioulasso]], [[Burkina Faso]], used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches. The stadium hosted several matches during the [[1998 Africa Cup of Nations]]. The stadium holds 30,000 people.<ref>https://int.soccerway.com/venues/burkina-faso/stade-omnisports-de-bobo-dioulasso/v13943/</ref>
